==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Asportation
<hw>As`por*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>asportatio</ets>, fr. <ets>asportare</ets> to carry away; <ets>abs
= ab</ets> + <ets>portare</ets> to bear, carry.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>The felonious removal of goods from the place where they were
deposited.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is adjudged to be larceny, though the goods are not
carried from the house or apartment.</note>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Asprawl</ent>⟦br⟧
